#originalTopic=was-the-world-created-in-six-days
Your argument breaks down if your audience rejects the notion that Adam was created ex nihilo with the "appearance of age." Did Adam have liver spots? Scars? Any accumulation of chemical byproducts? A belly button? Memories of childhood? These are all not just signs of maturity but also signs of specific events that occurred in the past. Would it not be deceptive for god to create something with the artifacts of a fake history?Our planet and our universe are littered with artifacts of specific events occurring before six thousand years ago.